# FVMP Theme — Development Rules

You are a senior WordPress block theme developer working on the FVMP training platform theme (formacion.fvmp.es). Always follow these rules strictly in every response.

## Project Overview

- **Type:** WordPress 6.9 Block Theme (Full Site Editing)
- **Stack:** PHP 8.2+, Vite, SCSS, Vanilla JS
- **Environment:** Local by Flywheel (Windows), Cursor IDE, Git Bash
- **Repo:** github.com/albaaguado/fvmp-tema
- **Branches:** `main` (production) → `develop` (integration) → `feature/*` (work)

## 1. WordPress Coding Standards

- Follow [WordPress PHP Coding Standards](https://developer.wordpress.org/coding-standards/wordpress-coding-standards/php/) strictly.
- Use tabs for indentation (not spaces) in PHP files.
- Use proper docblocks for all functions, classes, and files.
- Use Yoda conditions: `if ( 'value' === $var )`.
- Always add spaces inside parentheses: `if ( $condition )`, not `if ($condition)`.
- Use single quotes for strings unless interpolation is needed.

## 2. Security — Nonces & Sanitization

- Every form submission MUST use `wp_nonce_field()` and `wp_verify_nonce()`.
- Every AJAX request MUST include and verify a nonce via `check_ajax_referer()`.
- ALWAYS sanitize input:
  - `sanitize_text_field()` for text inputs
  - `absint()` for integers
  - `sanitize_email()` for emails
  - `esc_url()` for URLs
  - `wp_kses_post()` for rich content
- ALWAYS escape output:
  - `esc_html()` for plain text
  - `esc_attr()` for attributes
  - `esc_url()` for URLs
  - `wp_kses_post()` for HTML content
- NEVER use `$_GET`, `$_POST`, `$_REQUEST` without sanitization.
- NEVER trust user input. Validate, sanitize, escape — always.

## 3. Prefixing — `doo_` Namespace

- ALL custom functions MUST be prefixed: `doo_function_name()`.
- ALL custom classes MUST be prefixed: `Doo_Class_Name`.
- ALL CSS custom classes MUST be prefixed: `.doo-component-name`.
- ALL custom hooks MUST be prefixed: `doo_action_name`, `doo_filter_name`.
- ALL script/style handles MUST be prefixed: `doo-main-style`, `doo-vite-script`.
- ALL custom post types, taxonomies, meta keys: `doo_cpt_name`, `doo_meta_key`.
- ALL database options: `doo_option_name`.

```php
// ✅ Correct
function doo_enqueue_styles() { ... }
class Doo_Theme_Setup { ... }
wp_enqueue_style( 'doo-main-style', ... );

// ❌ Wrong
function enqueue_styles() { ... }
class ThemeSetup { ... }
wp_enqueue_style( 'main-style', ... );
```

## 4. Vulnerability Prevention

- Never use `eval()`, `extract()`, or `unserialize()` with user data.
- Never expose WordPress version, debug info, or file paths in production.
- Use `current_user_can()` for all permission checks before actions.
- Use prepared statements for any direct DB queries: `$wpdb->prepare()`.
- Disable file editing in production: `DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT`.
- Use Content Security Policy headers when possible.
- Validate file uploads: check MIME type, extension, and size.

## 5. Asset Enqueuing

- NEVER hardcode `<link>` or `<script>` tags in templates.
- ALWAYS use `wp_enqueue_style()` and `wp_enqueue_script()`.
- Use `wp_enqueue_scripts` hook for frontend assets.
- Use `admin_enqueue_scripts` hook for admin assets.
- Use versioning from Vite manifest for cache busting.
- Load scripts with `defer` or `in_footer` when possible.

```php
function doo_enqueue_assets() {
    $manifest = doo_get_vite_manifest();

    wp_enqueue_style(
        'doo-main-style',
        get_template_directory_uri() . '/dist/' . $manifest['src/scss/main.scss']['file'],
        array(),
        null
    );

    wp_enqueue_script(
        'doo-main-script',
        get_template_directory_uri() . '/dist/' . $manifest['src/js/main.js']['file'],
        array(),
        null,
        true
    );
}
add_action( 'wp_enqueue_scripts', 'doo_enqueue_assets' );
```

## 6. SCSS Architecture

- Use SCSS (Sass), NEVER plain CSS for source files.
- Follow 7-1 pattern structure:

```
src/scss/
├── abstracts/
│   ├── _variables.scss      ← Maps WP CSS custom properties
│   ├── _mixins.scss         ← Reusable mixins (breakpoints, etc.)
│   └── _functions.scss
├── base/
│   ├── _reset.scss
│   └── _typography.scss
├── components/
│   ├── _buttons.scss
│   ├── _cards.scss
│   └── _forms.scss
├── layout/
│   ├── _header.scss
│   ├── _footer.scss
│   └── _hero.scss
├── pages/
│   ├── _home.scss
│   ├── _formacion-continua.scss
│   ├── _fap.scss
│   └── _pim.scss
├── vendors/
│   └── _lucide.scss
└── main.scss               ← Imports everything
```

- Use WordPress CSS custom properties from theme.json in SCSS:

```scss
// In _variables.scss — reference WP design tokens
$color-teal: var(--wp--preset--color--teal);
$color-navy: var(--wp--preset--color--navy);
$color-red-cta: var(--wp--preset--color--red-cta);
$font-inter: var(--wp--preset--font-family--inter);
$spacing-30: var(--wp--preset--spacing--30);
```

## 7. Code Language — English Only

- ALL code MUST be written in English: variable names, function names, class names, comments, docblocks.
- Git commit messages in English.
- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `style:`, `chore:`.
- File and folder names in English, lowercase, kebab-case.
- HTML comments in block templates can be bilingual if needed for clarity.

```php
// ✅ Correct
function doo_get_training_programs() { ... }
// Retrieves active training programs from the database.

// ❌ Wrong
function doo_obtener_programas_formacion() { ... }
// Obtiene los programas de formación activos.
```

## 8. Vite Configuration

- Vite compiles SCSS → CSS and bundles JS.
- Output goes to `/dist/` folder.
- Vite generates a `manifest.json` for cache-busted asset paths.
- In development: Vite dev server with HMR (Hot Module Replacement).
- In production: `npm run build` generates optimized files.

### Vite Dev Server (development)

- Runs on `http://localhost:5173`.
- Auto-refreshes browser on SCSS/JS/PHP/HTML changes.
- PHP helper function detects dev vs production mode.

### Required Vite helper in functions.php:

```php
/**
 * Check if Vite dev server is running.
 *
 * @return bool True if dev server is active.
 */
function doo_is_vite_dev() {
    return defined( 'DOO_VITE_DEV' ) && DOO_VITE_DEV;
}

/**
 * Get Vite manifest for production asset paths.
 *
 * @return array Parsed manifest data.
 */
function doo_get_vite_manifest() {
    $manifest_path = get_template_directory() . '/dist/.vite/manifest.json';

    if ( ! file_exists( $manifest_path ) ) {
        return array();
    }

    return json_decode( file_get_contents( $manifest_path ), true );
}
```

## 9. Backup System

- Before modifying any existing theme file, create a backup copy.
- Backups go to `/backups/` folder with timestamp.
- The BAT script handles this automatically.
- `/backups/` is in `.gitignore` — never committed.

## 10. Browser Reload

- In development, Vite HMR handles automatic browser refresh.
- SCSS changes: hot-replaced without full reload (instant).
- PHP/HTML template changes: full page reload (automatic).
- No manual browser refresh needed during development.

## 11. BAT Scripts

- Provide `.bat` files for Windows workflows.
- All scripts go in `/bin/` folder.
- Scripts must include error handling and colored output.

### Required scripts:

```
bin/
├── dev.bat          ← Starts Vite dev server + opens Local site
├── build.bat        ← Runs production build
├── backup.bat       ← Creates timestamped backup of modified files
└── deploy.bat       ← Builds + commits + pushes to current branch
```

